<P>
   Add N.Y. Times News Service budget for papers of Monday, Aug.
10:
</P>
<P>
   CULTURE
</P>
<P>
   (Coded e)
</P>
<P>
   WAR-MOVIES (Undated) _ Vincent Canby takes an in-depth look at
the genre of war movies, with emphasis on Spielberg's latest opus.
</P>
<P>
   DICKEY-BOOK-REVIEW (Undated) _ Christopher Lehmann-Haupt reviews
``Summer of Deliverance: A Memoir of Father and Son'' by
Christopher Dickey.
</P>
<P>
   FINANCIAL
</P>
<P>
   (Coded f)
</P>
<P>
   MARKET-SMALLSTOCKS (Undated) _ While the larger, well-known
stocks of companies like Coca-Cola and Philip Morris have been
battered for much of the last month, the stocks of smaller
companies have suffered much more. The Dow Jones industrial
average, a large-stock gauge, fell about 9 percent from its high in
mid-July, while the Russell 2000 index of small stocks fell nearly
20 percent from its high in April. A study by Salomon Smith Barney
showed that the vast majority of small issues, with market values
of less than $250 million, had fallen 45 percent on average from
their peak through Aug. 4. The mounting evidence has prompted some
Wall Street analysts to talk about a darker side of the bull market
and even to suggest that a bear market is in the offing. By David
Barboza.
</P>
<P>
   BELL-DATA-ASSESS (Undated) _ Analysis: the politics and policy
behind the FCC's decision to let the Bells keep their data networks
to themselves. By Seth Schiesel.
</P>
<P>
   CYBERCASH (Undated) _ Cybercash has survived by adapting to the
less sophisticated but far more flexible security technology that
was eventually embraced throughout the Web. And though it is still
in the red, Cybercash has managed to take its stock pubic and to
grow by merging with a competitor. By Peter Wayner.
</P>
<P>
   AOL-MARKETPLACE (Undated) _ Behind the rise and fall of America
Online's stock. By Saul Hansell
</P>
<P>
   INVEST-SCAMS (Undated) _ The FTC plans to crack down on
entertainment industry investment scams. By Edward Wyatt.
</P>
<P>
   ECON-CALENDAR (Undated) _ Key government figures this week.
</P>
<P>
   BOND-CALENDAR (Undated) _ The week's planned offerings.
</P>
<P>
   EQUITIES (Undated) _ Equity issues coming to market this week.
</P>
<P>
   DIVIDEND-MEETINGS (Undated) _ Major meetings this week.
</P>
<P>
   BIZGLANCE (Undated) _ Major financial stories at a glance.
</P>
<P>
   PATENTS (Undated) _ The weekly patents column. By Sabra
Chartrand.
</P>
<P>
   MEDIA-BUSINESS
</P>
<P>
   (Coding varies.)
</P>
<P>
   GOLDEN-BOOKS-MEDIA (Undated) _ How Richard Snyder, and
investors, are doing with his stewardship of Golden Books. By
Geraldine Fabrikant and Doreen Carvajal.
</P>
<P>
   ALASKA-MAN-MEDIA (Undated) _ Restless times for Alaska Man, the
magazine that promotes the state's high proportion of single men,
for women who might like the odds. By Lisa Napoli.
</P>
