   AFRICA BOMBINGS:
</P>
<P>
   AFRICA-BOMBINGS (Nairobi, Kenya) _ American diplomats, soldiers,
intelligence officers and law-enforcement personnel from around the
world streamed into Nairobi on Sunday to shore up a shell-shocked
American Embassy, secure the shattered mission and search for clues
in the terrorist bombing that killed at least 190 people and
injured more than 4,000. By Tim Weiner.
</P>
<P>
   AFRICA-VICTIMS (Nairobi, Kenya) _ African families grieve for
those lost in the bombings. By James C. McKinley Jr.
</P>
<P>
   AFRICA-EMBASSY (Nairobi, Kenya) _ A reconstruction of what was
happening inside the American Embassy when the bomb went off. By
Raymond Bonner.
</P>
<P>
   AFRICA-U.S. (Washington) _ Albright, Cohen, Berger, Pickering on
the Sunday talk shows; plus Washington developments on the
bombings. By Philip Shenon.
</P>
<P>
   AFRICA-TERROR (Washington) _ Questions about the blasts, most of
them unanswered: what did the terrorists want; why they did it; why
they did it in Africa; what it means; why no credible group has yet
stepped forward to take credit. By James Risen.
</P>
<P>
   AFRICA-EVACUATE (Landstuhl, Germany) _ Injured Americans and
Kenyan Embassy employees arrive in Germany for medical aid. By
Craig R. Whitney.
</P>
<P>
   AFRICA-TANZANIA (Dar es Salaam) _ Investigation developments in
Dar es Salaam. By Jane Perlez.
</P>
<P>
   AFRICA-VICTIMS-U.S. (Undated) _ The U.S. victims and their
families.
</P>
