<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-HERBERT-COLUMN-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
COMMENTARY: THE HATE VIRUS 
</HEADLINE>
  (js) 
 By BOB HERBERT   
 c.1998 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK _ The purpose of the march, according to its
organizers, is to bring black and Latino youngsters from all over
the city and all around the country to Harlem to loudly protest
such pervasive evils as police brutality, job discrimination and
substandard educational opportunities.
</P>
<P>
   A worthy goal. But to pull this off safely and successfully, it
would help if you had leaders as conscientious and disciplined as,
say, Martin Luther King, Roy Wilkins, Whitney Young, John Lewis.
</P>
<P>
   But those are names from a brave and glorious past. Times have
changed. Once there was jazz and blues. Now there is gangsta rap.
And the so-called Million Youth March scheduled for Sept. 5 is
being led by one Khalid Abdul Muhammad.
</P>
<P>
   ``The so-called Jew claims that there were six million in Nazi
Germany. I am here today to tell you that there is absolutely no
evidence, no proof. There is absolutely no evidence to
substantiate, to prove that six million so-called Jews lost their
lives in Nazi Germany.''
</P>
<P>
   That was Muhammad speaking at San Francisco State University on
May 21, 1997.
</P>
<P>
   Same speech: ``Don't let no hooked-nose, bagel-eating,
lox-eating, perpetrating-a-fraud so-called Jew who just crawled out
of the ghettoes of Europe just a few days ago ...''
</P>
<P>
   Same speech: ``Who's pimping the world? The hairy hands of the
Zionist in the world.''
</P>
<P>
   Different speech, this one on the weekend before the Million Man
March in Washington in October 1995: ``Look at it, so-called Jew.
Look at it, imposter Jew. Somebody must call you what you are.
Somebody must look you in your cold lying blue eyes and pull the
cover off of you today. I don't give a damn about you and I will
give you hell from the cradle to the grave.''
</P>
<P>
   Muhammad, a former Nation of Islam official, has also made
sickening comments about rabbis and circumcision and was
disciplined by Louis Farrakhan after making a speech in which he
referred to Jews as ``bloodsuckers.''
</P>
<P>
   There is a big controversy now over Muhammad's desire to hold
his march, which would move through the heart of Harlem, along the
37 blocks of Malcolm X Boulevard between 147th Street and Central
Park North. Nearly everyone agrees that no matter how repellent his
views, Muhammad has a First Amendment right to march, but the exact
time and place are subject to reasonable regulation by the city.
</P>
<P>
   At the moment, the city is being led by one Rudolph Giuliani.
For him, this is an easy call. We are headed for a showdown.
</P>
<P>
   ``From my point of view,'' said the mayor, ``this is a hate
march.''
</P>
<P>
   The city has refused to grant Muhammad and his fellow organizers
a permit for a march on Malcolm X Boulevard. Officials have offered
instead to authorize a gathering at a different site, perhaps Van
Cortlandt Park in the Bronx or Randalls Island.
</P>
<P>
   The response from a colleague of Muhammad was as follows: ``The
Constitution does not say that Mayor Adolph Giuliani can determine
the time and place of the execution of our free speech and
assembly.''
</P>
<P>
   The organizers insist the march will go on as planned.
</P>
<P>
   So what happens next?
</P>
<P>
   It would be helpful if some prominent African-American leaders,
faced with the grotesque reality of a virulent anti-Semite playing
Pied Piper to the nation's black children, would stand up and say
enough is enough. This is wrong. This is not what our community
stands for, and it is not a message that we will allow to be fed to
our young.
</P>
<P>
   Rep. Charles Rangel, no ally of Giuliani, has denounced
Muhammad, saying, ``We don't need anybody preaching hatred in
Harlem.'' A few other black officials have issued more or less
muffled statements about not condoning Muhammad's rhetoric.
</P>
<P>
   More voices need to be heard, and they need to be louder and
more forceful. It needs to be made clear that Muhammad's type of
leadership is a virus that is potentially as debilitating to the
black community as HIV.
</P>
<P>
   It would also be helpful if public officials more skilled at
negotiating than Giuliani were allowed to play significant roles in
resolving the problem of when and where Muhammad is allowed to have
his say.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
