<SLUG> BC-MIRAMAX-NEWYORKER-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
TINA BROWN CHOOSES EDITOR FOR MIRAMAX MAGAZINE 
</HEADLINE>
  (js) 
 c.1998 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK _ Tina Brown, who recently resigned as editor of The
New Yorker, has chosen one of her longtime colleagues to be
executive editor of her new monthly magazine at Miramax, which is
due out in September 1999.
</P>
<P>
   David Kuhn, 38, the features and special issues editor at The
New Yorker, was appointed Friday as executive editor and vice
president of the new magazine. He will also be vice president of
Ms. Brown's and Ronald Galotti's new multimedia division within
Miramax, which will include the magazine unit and units for books,
television specials and feature films.
</P>
<P>
   ``David Kuhn's enterprise and imagination are a great fit in a
company that requires a lot of lateral thinking,'' Ms. Brown said
in a statement.
</P>
<P>
   The position seems, in many ways, tailored for Kuhn, who has
experience with film as well as several years in publishing. Before
going to The New Yorker, part of Advance Publications, in June
1994, he spent two years developing film material as a production
executive at Longview Entertainment, a company affiliated with
Universal/MCA.
</P>
<P>
   Before that, Kuhn spent seven years as an editor at Vanity Fair,
under Ms. Brown's leadership there.
</P>
<P>
   ``It really does kind of combine everything I have done
professionally since I started working in magazines, including my
two years in the movie business,'' said Kuhn, who starts in
September. ``I feel over the moon and sad that I'm leaving The New
Yorker, which has been an unbelievable ride.''
</P>
<P>
   Kuhn will be involved in the day-to-day running of the magazine
_ hiring, assigning articles and editing. Kuhn said it was too soon
to discuss a concrete vision for the magazine _ or a title. ``It's
something we have only talked about in the abstract,'' he said.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
